                "                Lanzhou (HIRFL)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Secondary ion beam of 10Be was produced by the",
                "Radioactive Ion Beam Line in Lanzhou (RIBLL) through",
                "the projectile fragmentation of a 59.62 A MeV 18O",
                "primary beam with an average intensity of 100 enA",
                "bombarded on a solid 853.96 mg/cm2 thick 9Be target.",
                "The 10Be beam was about 92% purity with an intensity",
                "of about 5.0E3 pps and an energy of 7.2 A MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "CH2 target (41.85 mg/cm2 thick)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PPAC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The incident angles of beam particles on the",
                "target were determined by extrapolating the hit",
                "positions recorded by two parallel-plate avalanche",
                "counters. PPACa and PPACb were 500 and 100 mm away",
                "from the target, respectively."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A 280-um-thick silicon detector was inserted in",
                "front of PPACa during the beam tuning to perform the",
                "particle identification with TOF."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "PS",
                "SISD",
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The scattered particles were",
                "detected by three downstream Delta E-E silicon",
                "telescopes (Set1, Set2 and Set3), which were placed",
                "at laboratory angles of +16, -16, and 0 deg with",
                "respect to the beam axis. The distances from the",
                "telescopes to the reaction target, with solid angles",
                "of 21, 20, and 21 msr, were set to be about 344, 349,",
                "and 345 mm, respectively. The Delta E detectors were",
                "position-sensitive double-sided-strip detectors",
                " (16x16, 3 mm width of each strip), measuring energy",
                "and two-dimensional position information of the",
                "recoiled particles with thickness of 301, 300, and",
                "149 um, respectively. The E silicon detectors, with",
                "thickness of 1533 and 1524 um in Set1 and Set2, and",
                "1528 um + 1538 um in Set3, measured the partial or",
                "whole energy."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two 50-um-thick plastic scintillators were",
                "used to measure the time of flight."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " To identify secondary beam"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TTM"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Thick-target technique"
              ]
            }
